    "daily_lesson": {
      "term": "Sector Diversification",
      "explanation_en": "Sector diversification means deliberately spreading investments across different industries \u2014 like tech, energy, materials, and telecom \u2014 so that a downturn in one sector doesn't drag down the whole portfolio. Today's three buys move the portfolio away from its heavy tech concentration (GOOGL, QQQ, AMZN) into uranium, rare earths, and telecom, each driven by different economic forces. This is especially important in a neutral market, where rotating into underrepresented sectors can improve risk-adjusted returns without taking on more overall risk.",
